TensorRT integration change log (eddy_matmulfreellm)
=====================================================

2026-05-07
----------
- Added tensorrt_generation.py: shared ONNX export, Triton-op patching, CUDAGraphAccelerator,
  ONNXTRTAccelerator, decode loop. TRT cache paths are derived from model_name (md5 prefix)
  so different checkpoints do not share one engine file.
- Refactored benchmark_trt.py to import from tensorrt_generation.py; behavior preserved;
  ONNXTRTAccelerator now receives model_name=MODEL_NAME for cache names.
- Updated generate.py: argparse (--model, --max-length, --iterations, --tensorrt,
  --rebuild-trt-engine); --tensorrt wraps inference in ONNXTRTAccelerator after HF load;
  optional --fixed-point still applied before TRT; exits with message if TRT/pycuda missing.
- Note: previous fixed cache /tmp/mmfreelm_jetson.engine is superseded by per-model paths
  under /tmp/mmfreelm_<hash>.{engine,onnx}.

- ONNX export: for seq_len > 1 the HGRN layer used Triton fused_recurrent_hgrn (not traceable).
  _export_onnx() temporarily binds naive_recurrent_hgrn in recurrent_fuse and hgrn_bit; restores
  after export. TRT engine then runs the exported graph (no Triton at inference).

generate.py run (sandbox): 2026-05-07 — HF DNS flake; model shards loaded from cache;
  CUDA failed in sandbox (NvRm / driver). Re-run on-device: python3 generate.py [--tensorrt].

generate.py run (device): 2026-05-07 — PyTorch path OK with --model ridger/MMfreeLM-370M.

TensorRT: ONNX export OK after naive recurrent patch; trt.Builder failed with CUDA error 35
  in this environment (TRT vs driver/context). Retry on a healthy JetPack CUDA stack.

Default ridger/MMfreeLM-2.7B: NvMapMemAlloc / allocator error when moving full model to GPU
  (OOM). Use --model ridger/MMfreeLM-370M on this device or free GPU memory and rerun.

2026-05-07 (FLOPs / inference)
---------------------------
- PureTorchFusedBitLinear: in eval mode cache one weight_quant() tensor (same as FusedBitLinear
  cached_weights); training still recomputes. Removes O(|W|) quant work every forward/token.
- ternary_quantize() now defers to mmfreelm.ops.fusedbitnet.weight_quant for bitwise parity with
  FusedBitLinear.
- PureTorchFusedRMSNormSwishGate: correct RMSNorm + weight * (o * sigmoid(o)) matching
  FusedRMSNormSwishGate Triton kernel; patch dispatcher no longer maps swish modules to plain
  RMSNorm (that mis-wired recurrent output as “residual”).
- generate.py: dense 2|θ| GFLOPS/s plus scaled “ternary MAC~” column using 1.58/16 heuristic.
- Patched vs full Triton logits can differ at ~0.5 relative L2 in FP16 (unfused vs fused kernels);
  acceptable for TRT/export path; use full Triton for bit-exact checks.

- GPU_MEMORY_NOTES.txt: ongoing VRAM/utilization checklist; generate.py gains --low-cpu-mem and
  --no-cache (use_cache=False) for marginal footprint / long-run savings.

